claim: Flublok (quadrivalent) was evaluated in the pivotal trial against Fluarix (quadrivalent standard-dose vaccine).
explanation: Two sets of pre- and post-vaccination line graphs showing the proportion of participants with ≥4-fold reduced hemagglutination inhibition (HI) titer egg/cell ratio across four influenza strains (A(H3N2), A(H1N1)pdm09, B/VIC, B/YAM) for two age groups (18–44 years and 45–64 years). Seven Year 1–Year 2 repeat vaccination arms are plotted with distinct symbols and colors: ccIIV4→ccIIV4, ccIIV4→RIV4, RIV4→ccIIV4, RIV4→RIV4, IIV4→ccIIV4, IIV4→RIV4, and IIV4→Fluzone IIV4. P values annotate significant pre-to-post changes for certain strains. Evidence: Legend shows IIV4→Fluzone IIV4 as the egg-based standard-dose comparator; no Fluarix quadrivalent is mentioned. The figure compares RIV4 (Flublok) against Fluzone IIV4, ccIIV4, and IIV4, but does not include Fluarix quadrivalent, so it does not support the claim Note: Resolution allows reading of legend and vaccine arm labels; absence of Fluarix is clear.
